The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 July is 292,278 (33,686.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 July, there were 1,490 new confirmed cases (171.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 July, there were 2,443 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 39% (953 fewer cases).
